column5: Georgian bay had some interesting things around we have seen the photoshop 2 pike in one well here's one with his balls on his head and these things flying over head.. and we caught a bunch a pike a few walleye (in the slot)and perch and rick bass to boot
Amazing what you can find when you fish beside a sewage outlet..
that might explain the deformities and sores in the pike
The pike looks like it has a 1/2 ounce bell sinker stuck to it's noggin.
That is just weird Terry.  But, some nice pickerel there and a nice shot of the turkey vulture  Joey
thanks the thing on it's head was filled with a liquid, really grossed me out  and I don't like turkey vultures circling over head...I have watched too many western movies....LOL
The trick is that you have to make yourself appear to be living, Terry.  By the way, nice shirt!
the older I get, the harder that is do ...LOL  and yes I still dress for success
Nice catches, lol you were fishing beside a sweage outlet LMAO !
Ya could of just fixed it's head up with a little surgery and showed the play by play. That would of been great!

Almost all the Pike we caught in Pickering had a gash or something taken out of their side...was weird, even a oos bass had a bite out of it. Do you think they pike bite eachother like this during the spawn?  Nice pictures Terry, definitely a weird looking pike lol
